con:method.name: GET
con:method.con:description: This resource is used to search our book database, and retrieve a set of objects related to your query. If there are no objects to return, the API will still return a 200 Status, but the "results" set will be an empty array and should be accounted for. Retrives an array of book objects scoped to title or authorID.

con:parameter.con:name: title
con:parameter.con:description: Title string to query. API will return both whole and partial matches dependent on the *fullMatch* parameter.

con:parameter.con:name: fullMatch
con:parameter.con:description: Boolean value of whether or not to return and exact match to the title query string.

con:parameter.con:name: authorID
con:parameter.con:description: ID of author to retrieve related books. Similar functionality can be found by querying */authors/{id}/books* if that level is desired.

con:method.name: POST
con:method.con:description: Returns object w/ID. POSTs a book object to our DB.

con:parameter.con:name: id
con:parameter.con:description: Book ID to update

con:method.name: GET
con:method.con:description: Returns single book object based on ID GETs a single book object.

con:method.name: DELETE
con:method.con:description: Deletes a created book based by ID - does not support name. Returns deleted object. DELETEs book object

con:method.name: PATCH
con:method.con:description: Updates a created book based by ID - does not support name. Returns deleted object. PATCHs book object

con:method.name: GET
con:method.con:description: Returns array based on author search params. GETs array of author objects based on query

con:parameter.con:name: first_name
con:parameter.con:description: first name search parameter

con:parameter.con:name: last_name
con:parameter.con:description: last name search parameter

con:method.name: POST

con:parameter.con:name: id
con:parameter.con:description: Book ID to update

con:method.con:description: Query for a specific author by ID. GETS an author object

con:method.name: getTestjobs
con:method.con:description: Use this operation to get results of the latest test runs stored in TestEngine.

con:parameter.con:name: fetch
con:parameter.con:description: Number of testjobs to return. Use `ALL to get all testjobs.

con:method.name: postProjectTestjob
con:method.con:description: Use this operation to send a ReadyAPI test project to TestEngine. You command TestEngine to execute the entire project, or an individual test suite or test case in it. The body of the request should be a ReadyAPI project file. Either send the .xml file as is, or zip it. A zip is needed to send in a composite project or when sending in a project with file dependencies.

con:parameter.con:name: testSuiteName
con:parameter.con:description: The name of the test suite to run.

con:parameter.con:name: testCaseName
con:parameter.con:description: The name of the test case to run.

con:parameter.con:name: environment
con:parameter.con:description: The target environment for test job.

con:parameter.con:name: async
con:parameter.con:description:
Specifies when TestEngine replies:
`true` - Immediately.
`false` - After the test job is over.

con:parameter.con:name: callback
con:parameter.con:description: The URL, to which the results will be posted.

con:parameter.con:name: clientCertFileName
con:parameter.con:description: The name of the separately provided client certificate file.

con:parameter.con:name: clientCertPassword
con:parameter.con:description: The password for the separately provided client certificate file.

con:parameter.con:name: projectPassword
con:parameter.con:description: The password used to decrypt an encrypted project file.

con:parameter.con:name: hostAndPort
con:parameter.con:description: The endpoint to be used for HTTP requests sent by this test, in the format host:[port].

con:parameter.con:name: tags
con:parameter.con:description: A comma-separated list of tags identifying the test cases to be run when executing the test

con:parameter.con:name: proxyHost
con:parameter.con:description: the HTTP proxy host

con:parameter.con:name: proxyPort
con:parameter.con:description: the proxy port

con:parameter.con:name: proxyUsername
con:parameter.con:description: the proxy username

con:parameter.con:name: proxyPassword
con:parameter.con:description: the proxy password

con:representation.con:description: Request contains unresolved files needed to execute the test job. It can be data sources, attachment or client certificates mentioned in test job but not provided in the request. Resend the request with all mentioned files.

con:method.name: deleteTestJobs
con:method.con:description: Delete jobs older than the specified date. If a date is not provided, test jobs older than a default number of days will be deleted. The default can be changed by changing `numberOfDaysToKeep` in the configuration file.

con:parameter.con:name: before
con:parameter.con:description: Testjobs older than this date/time will be deleted.

con:method.name: cancelTestjob
con:method.con:description: Use this operation to stop the run specified by testjobId. You can find the testjobId in the response to your testjob request, or you can send a GET /testjobs request to the TestEngine.

con:parameter.con:name: testjobId
con:parameter.con:description: The unique identifier of a test job

con:method.name: getTestjobReport
con:method.con:description: Use this operation to get information on the testjob specified by testjobId. You can find in the response to your testjob request , or you can send a GET /testjobs request to TestEngine.

con:parameter.con:name: testjobId
con:parameter.con:description: The unique identifier of a test job

con:method.name: getTransactions
con:method.con:description: Use this operation to get transaction logs (individual request and response of executed test steps) of the test job specified by test jobID. You can find it in the response of your test job request , or you can send a GET /testjobs/{testjobId}/logs request to TestEngine.

con:parameter.con:name: testjobId
con:parameter.con:description: The unique identifier of a test job

con:method.name: getTransaction
con:method.con:description: A particular test job of a test step is referred as transaction. Use this operation to get the request and response for a transaction in HAR format.

con:parameter.con:name: testjobId
con:parameter.con:description: The unique identifier of a test job

con:parameter.con:name: transactionId
con:parameter.con:description: The id of the transaction (test step test job) to get the message exchange (request and response) for.
